The paper deals with a defense mechanism against undetected infiltration in cyber-physical systems, which is a topic related to cybersecurity (cs.CR). The proposed approach involves designing the outputs of sensors that monitor the system's state, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of game-theoretic hierarchical equilibrium and semi-definite programming, which are topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the incorporation of secure sensor design with other defense mechanisms, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE).
